Text:
@Payrus123

What do you mean Valve is monitoring it? Are they going to send an ISP letter? Doesn't that usually take a few days. and even if they are, ISP letters are meaningless.

Or are you referring to something else?

@AsILayDaing   I'm not sure why the Bastion.exe sets off your anti-ware. I have scanned it with Ad-aware, Malwarebytes and AVG 2011 and nothing has shown up. I've installed it and it runs perfectly. However NFOviewer.exe and the update immediately set off Ad-aware.

@All  But lets be realistic here:

1)What do any of you need a simple supposed info file for. You came here for an executable program not info files.

2) This game was just released on 08/06/2011 and this torrent was uploaded on the same date. When have you ever heard of a game being released with an update at the same time? Never. Perhaps one will be release in the same week if they get serious feedback from the community regarding some serious bugs but that's it. Some common sense would tell you all this. 

Bottom line:

Educate yourselves a bit before you try to download any software and make sure that all of the files your trying to download and use are actually part of the original software package. Cracked executes not included of course. And always scan the file with multiple anti-ware programs. Finally, when in doubt and unsure, just don't use it.
